:"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":0},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":568163,"mol_weight":0,"name":"CutSmart\u00ae Buffer","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/neb.com","sku":"B7204S","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":0},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":581618,"mol_weight":0,"name":"BHIS (34 g BHI and 91.1 g sorbitol in 1 L deionized water pH 7.2)","linfor":"","url":"http:\/\/null","sku":null,"cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":" ","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":0},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"{\"blocks\":[{\"key\":\"5jor\",\"text\":\"Introducing NLP14a in the genome of B. mycoides:  In order to create plasmid pYCR-gamyNLP, the backbone of Pycr will be digested with the PCR product of gamy_Fw and gamy_Rv to produce the pYCR_gamy (CRISPR vector containing the gRNA). The NLP14a sequence will be ordered from Twist Biosciences And PCR-amplified with the primers NLP_Fw and NLP_Rv. The resulting PCR product, as well as the pYCR_gamy vector will be digested with SfiI. The digested mixtures will be ligated using T4 ligase. \",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"length\":49,\"offset\":0,\"style\":\"bold\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"34qtr\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"5evts\",\"text\":\"Kill switch cloning: The suggested kill switch mechanism is based on Trp auxotrophic strains as well as a toxin-antitoxin mechanism. The toxin will be introduced in the genome using crispr in place of trpE. The antitoxin will be maintained as a cytoplasmic plasmid (pAD-YqcF) and expressed only in the presence of solanine. Unfortunately, to the best of our knowledge, no operator that binds solanine of B. mycoides has been described in literature. If it is provebn that no such operator is present, we suggest on oly keeping the tryptophan dependence strategy.  \",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"length\":21,\"offset\":0,\"style\":\"bold\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"4qbf1\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"cq2uf\",\"text\":\"The plasmid pAD-KPS12-Pman will used as a starting point for introducing the antitoxin gene (ygcF) in B. mycoides. The vector will be cut with XbaI and SphI and ligated with the PCR amplified ygcF (using ygcF_Fw and ygcF_Rv as primers). In order to make the antitoxin expression inducible by solanine we plan on replacing the mannose inducible promoter with a promoter induced by solanine. To accomplish this, we will use the primers Psol_Fw and Psol_Rv to amplify the solanine promoter. The pAD-ygcFvector will be digested with EcoRI and XbaI, and ligated with the solanine promoter PCR product that will be digested as well with the up mentioned restriction enzymes. \",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"length\":13,\"offset\":102,\"style\":\"italic\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"6pds5\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"20h85\",\"text\":\"In order to create plasmid pYCR-gtrpEYqcG plasmid, the backbone of Pycr will be digested with BsaI and ligated with the annealing product of gtrpe_Fw and gtrpe_Rv to produce the pYCR_gtrp (CRISPR vector containing the gRNA). Synthetic dna for yqcG will be ordered from Twist Biosciences and PCR-amplified with the primers Yqcg_Fw and Ygcg_Rv. The resulting PCR product, as well as the pYCR_gtrpE vector will be digested with SfiI. The digested mixtures will be ligated using T4 ligase. \",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[{\"length\":5,\"offset\":242,\"style\":\"italic\"}],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"7n4q0\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]},{\"key\":\"bhbo0\",\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"align-left\",\"depth\":0,\"inlineStyleRanges\":[],\"entityRanges\":[],\"data\":[]}],\"entityMap\":[]}","changed_on":1603539639}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1060455,"guid":"74663910155211EB963C678171F332ED","previous_id":1060454,"previous_guid":"4BE87840155211EB963C678171F332ED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"48BF14D2AC89405799403404D08AD079","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transform final construct in B. mycoides M2E_15"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"391700C9D3314CAF8C4C438CBB90D50F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Plate on LB agar containing erythromycin<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Grow at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> overnight<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"BC36E510156011EB963C678171F332ED","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":28,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1060456,"guid":"A34BAF80155211EB963C678171F332ED","previous_id":1060455,"previous_guid":"74663910155211EB963C678171F332ED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1E45BB712C994CDDAEF8F42BAD2EB878","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transform final construct in B. mycoides M2E_15"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3BC2F82DB5B34D788AFC0B11790CDADE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Pick colonies and test them by colony PCR <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If the expected band size is present, purify the plasmid and sequence<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1060467,"guid":"3B7A4C50155B11EB963C678171F332ED","previous_id":1060456,"previous_guid":"A34BAF80155211EB963C678171F332ED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A7B1CBA0240C47BDB75760A427A63E76","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transform final construct in B. mycoides M2E_15"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2A9278106A93459883501AFB277160C8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Grow the colonies with the expected sequence on liquid LB + erythromycin + manose <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2C3AE3C0156111EB963C678171F332ED","order_id":2,"type_id":33,"title":"shaker","source":{"duration":43200,"guid":"2C3AE3C0156111EB963C678171F332ED","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"shaker":"200","start":null,"temperature":"28","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":33}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1060469,"guid":"C0C2EF20155B11EB963C678171F332ED","previous_id":1060467,"previous_guid":"3B7A4C50155B11EB963C678171F332ED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8FEC0D64F4D84DE28A76A89965E53D0C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transform final construct in B. mycoides M2E_15"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FAF16197495F4788B8FFD5A290865E92","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Next day pick colonies in BHI medium (without antibiotic) and grow at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">overnight <\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E2854D50156111EB963C678171F332ED","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":37,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1060501,"guid":"A16A2070156111EB963C678171F332ED","previous_id":1060469,"previous_guid":"C0C2EF20155B11EB963C678171F332ED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1808CED132D840D3BE79E9E3C3153CC6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Transform final construct in B. mycoides M2E_15"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"253AD3B29E22412381422CC20D0D76CC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dilute the liquid cultures and plate them on LN (no antibiotic)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">grow overnight st<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E0FED460156111EB963C678171F332ED","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":37,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Introducing NLP14a in the genome of B. mycoides: <\/span><span> In order to create plasmid pYCR-gamyNLP, the backbone of Pycr will be digested with the PCR product of gamy_Fw and gamy_Rv to produce the pYCR_gamy (CRISPR vector containing the gRNA). The NLP14a sequence will be ordered from Twist Biosciences And PCR-amplified with the primers NLP_Fw and NLP_Rv. The resulting PCR product, as well as the pYCR_gamy vector will be digested with SfiI. The digested mixtures will be ligated using T4 ligase. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Kill switch cloning: <\/span><span>The suggested kill switch mechanism is based on Trp auxotrophic strains as well as a toxin-antitoxin mechanism. The toxin will be introduced in the genome using crispr in place of trpE. The antitoxin will be maintained as a cytoplasmic plasmid (pAD-YqcF) and expressed only in the presence of solanine. Unfortunately, to the best of our knowledge, no operator that binds solanine of B. mycoides has been described in literature. If it is provebn that no such operator is present, we suggest on oly keeping the tryptophan dependence strategy.  <\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><span>In order to create plasmid pYCR-gtrpEYqcG plasmid, the backbone of Pycr will be digested with BsaI and ligated with the annealing product of gtrpe_Fw and gtrpe_Rv to produce the pYCR_gtrp (CRISPR vector containing the gRNA). Synthetic dna for<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> yqcG<\/span><span> will be ordered from Twist Biosciences and PCR-amplified with the primers Yqcg_Fw and Ygcg_Rv. The resulting PCR product, as well as the pYCR_gtrpE vector will be digested with SfiI. The digested mixtures will be ligated using T4 ligase<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">Protocol was adapted after a paper of Yi et  al., 2018<\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\">1. Yi, Y., Li, Z., Song, C. & Kuipers, O. P. Exploring plant-microbe interactions of the rhizobacteria Bacillus subtilis and Bacillus mycoides by use of the CRISPR-Cas9 system. Environ. Microbiol. 20, 4245\u20134260 (2018). <\/div><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1603539638}